### Grid layout
Use CSS grid: `gridTemplateColumns: 'repeat(auto-fill, minmax(280px, 1fr))'`, gap 12px.

## Formulation Detail (selectedFormulation !== null)

When selectedFormulation is set to any formulation id, show this INSTEAD of the current sub-view.

Look up: `const f = FORMULATIONS.find(x => x.id === selectedFormulation);`

### Back button
"← My vault" — 13px, cursor pointer, color green, margin-bottom 16px.
onClick: `setSelectedFormulation(null)`

### Header
- Name: fontFamily serif, 24px, rgba(255,255,255,0.9)
- "Documented {f.documented} · 🔒 Private" — 12px muted, margin-bottom 16px

### Conditions
Row of green tag pills (same style as vault cards but slightly larger: 3px 10px padding)

### Ingredients card
Card with header "Ingredients ({f.ingredients.length})".
Map ingredients, each item:
- local name (14px, bold, rgba(255,255,255,0.8))
- " — " + english name (14px, rgba(255,255,255,0.5))
- botanical name below (12px, italic, rgba(255,255,255,0.3), fontFamily serif)
- 8px padding-bottom, border-bottom if not last

### Preparation card
Card with header "Preparation".
- Text (13px, rgba(255,255,255,0.6), line-height 1.6)
- Below text: button "🎤 Play original voice recording" — rounded 8px, padding 8px 16px, bg rgba(255,255,255,0.04), border rgba(255,255,255,0.08), 12px font, cursor pointer
- onClick: toggle a `playingAudio` state. When playing, show an animated waveform (5-7 div bars, each 3px wide, varying heights, CSS animation oscillating heights) + "Playing... 1:12". Click again to stop.

### Dosing card
Card with header "Dosing". Text content.

### Warnings
If warnings exist: row of terra pills with ⚠️ prefix.
Style: bg rgba(158,74,47,0.12), color #F87171, padding 3px 10px, 10px font bold, rounded 6px.

### Expected outcome card
Card with header "Expected outcome".
- "⏱️ {timeline}" — badge with gold bg/border/text
- Success indicators as green pills

### 📊 Outcomes section
Card with header "Patient outcomes".

**Large effectiveness:**
- {effectiveness}% — fontFamily serif, 48px, color #4ADE80

**Outcome bar:** (28px height, same style as dashboard but bigger)

**Legend:** below bar

**Stats row** (3 columns, border-top, padding-top 12px):
- "4.2" / "Avg days to improvement"
- "91%" / "Completed full course"
- "{sideEffects.count}" / "Side effects ({sideEffects.severity})"

**Confidence:** badge — if tracked >= 200 "🟢 High confidence ({tracked}+ outcomes)", if >= 50 "🟡 Medium ({tracked})", else "🔴 Low ({tracked})"

**Monthly trend:** CSS bar chart from f.monthlyOutcomes.
Flex row, align-items flex-end, gap 6px, height 120px.
Each month: flex column, align center, flex 1.
- Tracked count above bar (10px, muted)
- Bar: width 100%, rounded 4px 4px 0 0, bg green, height = (eff / 100) * 100px
- Month label below (9px, muted)

### Research interest
If f.researchInterest > 0:
Card with indigo tint (bg rgba(45,75,142,0.06), border rgba(45,75,142,0.12)).
"🔬 {f.researchInterest} researchers have expressed interest in this formulation."
Button "View requests →" (does nothing, just shows UI)

### Action buttons
Row with 8px gap:
- "✏️ Edit" — outline button
- "📤 Share" — outline button
Both are UI-only, no action needed.

